## Deep Analysis (this session continuation)

### Game Mechanics Confirmed
- Score = (network_junctions - 1) per tick, normalized by max_steps
- 4 clips ships at map corners, scramble 1 junction/70 steps each
- Clips also ALIGN neutral junctions (build enemy network)
- Game is NON-DETERMINISTIC beyond seed (same seed gives 0.00 or 4.73)

### Aligner Time Breakdown (seed 1337, 5000 steps)
- 49.2% find_neutral_junction (searching)
- 29.2% align_junction (traveling + aligning)
- 14.4% deposit_cargo
- 4.0% retreat_to_hub
- Only 29% productive alignment time!

### Changes Applied (v59)
- Retreat margin 28→32 (reduces deaths from 8 to 0-3)
- Patrol: staleness 100 (not 50), range 25, prioritizes was-friendly junctions
- Idle aligners mine instead of exploring randomly
- Deposit only if within 5 tiles
- Smooth economy scaling (5→4→3 aligners as resources drop)
- Ship danger zone decay (150 steps)
- Uploaded v59 to tournament

### Experiments That Didn't Help
- Aggressive hub proximity scoring: too few close junctions, score drops
- Phase-based ramp (2/3/5): slower start without benefit
- 6 aligners: economy collapses
- Frontier-directed exploration: sends aligners too far

### Key Insight
- Main bottleneck is 49% of aligner time SEARCHING (find_neutral_junction)
- Ships at corners build expanding frontiers; hub-proximal junctions safest
- Game variance is extreme (0.00 to 6.00) — need 20+ game averages

